Equal sides: All four sides of a square are equal in length. 
Right angles: Each angle in a square measures 90 degrees. 
Parallel opposite sides: Opposite sides of a square are parallel to each other. 
Bisecting diagonals: The diagonals of a square bisect each other. 
Equal diagonals: Both diagonals of a square are equal in length. 
Isosceles triangles: Each diagonal divides the square into two congruent isosceles right triangles. 
Angle sum: The sum of all interior angles of a square is 360 degrees. 
